Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper deals with VANET (Vehicular Ad-hoc Networks) which is a subfield of networking. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed approach involves the integration of Grid Computing which falls under this sub-category. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may involve the use of algorithms for traffic routing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may involve the use of control systems for traffic management. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - VANETs are vulnerable to security threats and the paper may address security issues related to traffic routing.
